args: It is taking some time to question the\nsuspect, so you must remain in the\nguardroom for the time being.
And so you are aware, we have guards\nposted outside the window; I recommend\nyou do not even think about escape.
They think me the ringleader of an\nassassination! How has it come to this?
*cough* Goodness, but it's dusty in here!\nI swear, good help is so hard to find...
Don't start squawking like that, darling,\nor you'll alert every guard for miles!

Oh, just to make a little apology.
Seems like you're only in this pickle
because you were chasing after little
ol' me during the ceremony.

You may not believe this, but I was only
there to see for myself what sort of work
you do now that you've hung up your
little throat-slitters.
Anyway, I'm just sorry as all get-out!
This state of affairs is not your doing,\nso you can save your apology.
Well, that's good to—oh, heck!\nI plumb near forgot to mention it!
Not to be the bearer of ill news, but that\nGrand Paladyn friend of yours looks to be\nin quite the precarious situation.
Well, I went to check on her before coming\nhere, and the poor thing was doubled over\nin pain and BEGGING for help.
Say, that gives me a dilly of an idea:\nlet's go see her! With my help, you'll be\nable to creep by the guard undetected.
I would give anything to help Elisanne,\nbut if I slip away, the suspicion upon me\nwill only grow more intense.

Honey, she was looking REAL bad.
Poor thing might kick the farm any second
now—can you live with yourself if you
don't take this chance to say good-bye?
Fie, but this is an impossible choice!\nWhat should I do...?
We managed to slip away unnoticed.\nThank Ilia for this incoming fog.
The local types are all holed up inside,\nwhat with the explosions and all—but ain't\nthat just a stroke of luck for us!
Yes, because it means we can make as\nmuch noise as we like without suspicion.\n...Doesn't it, Dorothy?
Honey, are you really pointing that\npigsticker of yours in MY direction?!
Inducing a person to kill a target without\ndirtying your own hands is one of your\nspecialties, is it not?

Oh, darling, you have this ALL wrong!
Also, hate to mention it, but the longer you
point that sword at me, the more likely it
is that your friend...you know? Dies alone?

Your story about Elisanne rang false on
too many levels, Dorothy. She would not
succumb to such a wound, nor would she
allow even a whimper to escape her lips.
You tried to kill the archbishop and frame\nme for it in order to have revenge for my\ndeigning to leave a former life behind.
Oh, honey, you are SO good!\nTell me, how long have you known?

From the moment you appeared in the
guardroom. I know you, Dorothy, and I
know you never could resist laughing
in the face of someone you framed.
But had I made a fuss then and there,\nit would've gotten the Templars involved.
So you pretended to believe me until you\nhad a chance to question me alone!\nOh, darling, you are just the BEST!

Here I was, all ready to kill you for
believing my absurd story, and you've
gone and turned the tables! I KNEW the
beast was still alive in you somewhere!
Oh, but I'm afraid I can't quite put a plus\non that A grade of yours. See, honey,\nthere's still one flaw in your deduction.
I had no intention of assassinating the\narchbishop—I just knew the Grand Paladyn\nwould risk her life in order to protect him.
But that would mean your real target is...
Yes indeed-y! Your little pal, Elisanne.\nAfraid I'm under some VERY strict orders\nto see that she takes the ol' dirt nap.

Now honey, you know I can't tell you that!
But I will give you one piece of advice:
abandon Elisanne now, before all of this
starts to turn TRULY ugly.
After all, she holds the key to perdition.
...Alex should be around here! Find her!
Ta-ta, Alex! Oh, and don't worry—I'll come\nby and see you again REAL soon.
Damn it all! I was hoping to capture her\nand find out the truth behind all of this!
Look there, on the ground!\nIt's a bloody dagger!

Observe the peculiar shape of the blade.
There can be no doubt this is the murder
weapon used to kill the perpetrator of the
assassination attempt.
Damn and damn again! Dorothy must have\nkilled the man to ensure his silence!
Alex clearly cast the dagger aside here.\nFind her at once, or none of us will ever\nbe fit to bear the name of Templar again!
I've no wish to cross blades with the\nTemplars. Time to make good my escape!
*huff* *puff* I should have eluded my\npursuers by now, but I cannot hope to\nkeep running away forever.
Dorothy is sure to target Elisanne again,\nand yet the Templars would rather die\nthan listen to anything I have to say.

It will only make trouble for my comrades
if I return to the Halidom, so I'll need to
capture Dorothy on my own. Ah, but she's
a tricky one, and no mistake.

Which means the only way to save Elly is
to expose the client who requested the
assassination in the first place—and in
so doing drag the truth into the light.
And my clue to finding the client is...
After all, she holds the key to perdition.

Common sense dictates the ＂key to
perdition＂ is connected to perditionists,
which means it's time for that man and
myself to have a little chat.
Ho, friend! I am a traveling man of the\ncloth—pray bless me with your charity.
Sorry, Father, but we're barely scraping\nby as it is. Try someone else.
Rrrgh! May they burn in the fires of\npurgatory! Damned impious wretches!
*sigh* To think I was once so close to the\nposition of archbishop and now find myself\nreduced to this paltry existence.
Ah! Perhaps that person there will take\nsome pity on a poor old man of the cloth.\nHo, friend! I am a traveling... Y-YOU!
